<br>
Weapon is a Velium Morning Star and I wield a shield of some kind, nothing special.<br>
<br>
I have reviewed the equipment list on the main site, but I don't have any idea what is the most important item to work toward.<br>
<br>
Also note that I have only enough money to get my 24 spells at the moment, but money is starting to flow a little better as the mobs that we are hunting are finally carrying decent loot.  And I will not have to buy any more spells for 5 levels after the next one.<br>
<br>
Thanks<br>
<br>
Dyrne Darkwood - Druid of Tunare<br>
Morell-Thule <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukresha.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kresha</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(1/17/01 8:02:38 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Equipment Questions</span><hr size=1> Well if you group much you might want to try grouping at 24 in Unrest and get a savant cap (AC 2 Wis 3) for yourself and the thick leather apron (AC 8) as well as some cash/fs/bronze armor/gossimer armor that drops to use to buy other pieces.<br>
<br>
Could also group in Permafrost at that level and get a runed circlet (AC 4 Wis 4), cold iron morningstar (9/35 1hb), etched ivory charm (neck AC 5, wis 2, str 2 from the jailmaster).  Easier to walk into Unrest and find a group than perma where you normally have to bring one.<br>
<br>
A group around 25 can also make good xp at the Ancient Croc spawn in UGuk and pickup gator arms for the casters and gator legs for the healers (AC 7 Wis 4).<br>
<br>
Can get plenty of FS grouping in Cazic Thule at that level.  Can partner/trio to get PBBs (AC 2 Wis 3) in beholders mage at that level.<br>
<br>
If solo your best bet might be fear kiting Adult Mammoths in Everfrost -- good xp (they run 22-26 in level) and the tusks sell for 8-11 plat so you could simply save up and buy that stuff.<br>
<br>
If you save a bit can also buy Foreman's tunic (AC 10, Wis 3, Str 3 for 100-200pp) and Braided Ivy Cords (AC 4 Wis 5 for 200-500pp) and one of the best items you can buy as a druid long before you can hunt it yourself usually, the Charred Guardian Shield (AC 10, Wis 9 for 300 to 500pp).  Plus the usual jewelry upgrades to plat ruby veil (Wis 7, Str 7), Plat jasper rings (Wis 6) and Gold Jasper Earrings (Wis 3).<br>
<br>
You may not be able to hunt all of em or afford em between 24 and 29, but you should be able to get many then and the rest by say level 34.<br>
<br>
